definition.value: A sorbic acid having trans-double bonds at positions 2 and 4; a food preservative that can induce cutaneous vasodilation and stinging upon topical application to humans. It is the most thermodynamically stable of the four possible geometric isomers possible, as well as the one with the highest antimicrobial activity.
One of four possible geometric isomers of sorbic acid, having cis-double bonds at positions 2 and 4.
One of four possible geometric isomers of sorbic acid, having cis- and trans-double bonds at positions 2 and 4 respectively.
One of four possible geometric isomers of sorbic acid, having trans- and cis-double bonds at positions 2 and 4 respectively.
An octadecynoic acid having its triple bond at position 6.
A heptenoic acid with the double bond at position 6.
A 2-heptenoic acid having the trans configuration.
A 2-heptenoic acid having the cis configuration.

A pentenoic acid having the double bond at position 3.
A pent-3-enoic acid in cis- configuration.
A pent-3-enoic acid in trans- configuration.
The 10-methochloride salt of 3,6-diaminoacridine. Note that a mixture of this compound with 3,6-diaminoacridine (proflavine) is known as acriflavine or neutral acriflavine.
